   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Boost charge mode can be entered manually through the system
interface or automatically if auto boost charge is enabled. For example,
boost charge can be activated automatically after a period of battery
operation or a discharge test. In boost charge the rectifier output
voltage is higher than in float charge.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">It is possible to inhibit
the change of charge mode. This inhibits both manual and automatic
change of charge mode. For more information please see <xref href="SDC_Boost_Charge_Inhibit_CPT_0000536862.dita"
                  scope="local"
                  type="concept"
                  class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
